    {
        "content": "<p>TartanLlama opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12736\">PR #12736</a> from <code>TartanLlama:sy/future-stream-thread</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The current thread is not set before lowering the results of stream/future reads, which can potentially call <code>realloc</code>.</p>\n<p>Putting this up as a draft for now as I'm off tomorrow, will add some tests for this on Monday.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 577553898,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1772730148
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>github-actions[bot] added the label <code>wasmtime:api</code> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12736\">PR #12736</a>.</p>",
        "id": 577595648,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1772744046
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12736#pullrequestreview-3899606651\">PR review</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Longer-term (@dicej you may have thoughts on this too) I feel like the juggling here is pretty brittle and it seems like we should have a new argument to <code>LowerContext::new</code> or something like that. I'm not sure if that would work well given all the various juggling involved, but might be something worth considering.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 577596117,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1772744226
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12736#discussion_r2892274888\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I think this argument is always <code>self.concurrent_state_mut().current_guest_thread()?</code>, so could the argument be dropped and that inlined directly below?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 577596120,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1772744226
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12736#discussion_r2892280776\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Mind leaving comments here, and above, for why the current thread is set?</p>\n<p>Also, is this something where we want to restore the previous thread after this finishes? </p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 577596121,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1772744226
    },
